text: <@U04AQA0QM8E>if I export my table and re-import will that do anything?
Not inherently. Rows without content still have associated metadata, so they’ll be imported and exported just like rows that contain content.

another question if you don’t mind. our website just got redone and when the company imported our blog posts they messed something up and now blogs are <http://domain.com/blog/blog/title-of-post|domain.com/blog/blog/title-of-post>
what is the best way to remove the extra /blog?

You’ll have to update the posts to remove the second `blog/` from their URL slugs. Depending on how many you have, your most efficient option might be to use <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/api/cms/blog-post|the Blog Post API> to update your posts in batch.
